cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the spread of health sentiments on a social network (Twitter) and uses statistical methods to measure the effects of social network variables on the spread of sentiments. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper may involve the development of software tools or algorithms for data collection and analysis on social networks. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper applies computational methods to study social phenomena (health behavior sentiments) on a social network. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may touch on issues related to privacy and security of personal health information on social networks. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a less likely category but possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques to analyze the sentiment of tweets related to health behavior.
